A continuous uniform (rectangular) distribution parameterised by a single RELATIVE half-width, futuram:uncertaintyLimit, symmetric about the quantity's best value: the support is [best x (1 - limit), best x (1 + limit)]. The form the FutuRaM reference dataset uses for every measured value (the source generator's note: 'we use a X% rectangular distribution'): a data-quality / confidence judgement gives a defensible +/- band, and the rectangular (maximum-entropy) distribution is the honest model when only a range is known (GUM type-B). It carries ONE scale parameter (the half-width) instead of futuram:UniformDistribution's two explicit endpoints (lowerBound/upperBound) -- those endpoints are DERIVED (best x (1 -/+ limit)), not stored. Its standard deviation is limit x best / sqrt(3) (the sigma of a uniform of half-width a is a/sqrt(3)) -- the source's stored uncertainty% (a relative sigma). Modelled as a continuous uniform (Apollo APOLLO_SV_00000257; alignment in apollo-futuram-bridge.ttl) and a futuram:Distribution; NOT a subclass of futuram:UniformDistribution, so it does not inherit that class's lowerBound/upperBound requirement (it parameterises the SAME family differently).:

